00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:05.970
We are told that the formula for
finding the perimeter of a

00:00:05.970 --> 00:00:12.180
rectangle is P is equal to 2l
plus 2w, where P is the

00:00:12.180 --> 00:00:16.520
perimeter, l is the length,
and w is the width.

00:00:16.520 --> 00:00:18.840
And just to visualize what
they're saying, and you might

00:00:18.840 --> 00:00:24.080
already be familiar with this,
let me draw a rectangle.

00:00:24.080 --> 00:00:27.080
That looks like a rectangle.

00:00:27.080 --> 00:00:31.780
And if this side's length is l,
then this side's length is

00:00:31.780 --> 00:00:33.230
also going to be l.

00:00:33.230 --> 00:00:38.140
And if this width is w, then
this width up here is w.

00:00:38.140 --> 00:00:40.690
And the perimeter is just how,
what is the distance if you

00:00:40.690 --> 00:00:43.460
were to go around
this rectangle?

00:00:43.460 --> 00:00:49.310
And so, that distance is going
to be this w plus this l, plus

00:00:49.310 --> 00:00:53.350
this w-- or that width--
plus this length.

00:00:53.350 --> 00:00:59.070
And if you have 1 w and you add
it to another w, that's

00:00:59.070 --> 00:01:00.320
going to give you 2 w's.

00:01:00.320 --> 00:01:01.940
So that's 2 w's.

00:01:01.940 --> 00:01:06.700
And then if you have 1 l, and
then you have another l,

00:01:06.700 --> 00:01:08.260
that's going to give you, if you
add them together, that's

00:01:08.260 --> 00:01:09.970
going to give you 2 l's.

00:01:09.970 --> 00:01:13.150
So the perimeter is going
to be 2 l's plus 2 w's.

00:01:13.150 --> 00:01:14.720
They just wrote it in a
different order than

00:01:14.720 --> 00:01:16.300
the way I wrote it.

00:01:16.300 --> 00:01:18.650
But the same thing, so hopefully
that makes sense.

00:01:18.650 --> 00:01:22.040
Now, their question is, rewrite
the formula so that it

00:01:22.040 --> 00:01:25.630
solves for width.

00:01:25.630 --> 00:01:29.050
So the formula, the way it's
written now, it says P is

00:01:29.050 --> 00:01:30.120
equal to something.

00:01:30.120 --> 00:01:33.770
They want us to write it so
it's, this w, right here, they

00:01:33.770 --> 00:01:38.410
want it to be w is equal to a
bunch of stuff with l's and

00:01:38.410 --> 00:01:40.210
P's in it, and maybe
some numbers there.

00:01:40.210 --> 00:01:43.240
So let's think about
how we can do this.

00:01:43.240 --> 00:01:48.260
So they tell us that P is
equal to 2 times l,

00:01:48.260 --> 00:01:50.380
plus 2 times w.

00:01:50.380 --> 00:01:53.300
We want to solve for w.

00:01:53.300 --> 00:01:56.750
Well, a good starting point
might be to get rid of the l

00:01:56.750 --> 00:01:58.630
on this side of the equation.

00:01:58.630 --> 00:02:00.790
And to get rid of it on that
side of the equation, we could

00:02:00.790 --> 00:02:05.050
subtract the 2l from both
sides of the equation.

00:02:05.050 --> 00:02:06.040
So let's do it this way.

00:02:06.040 --> 00:02:08.259
So you subtract 2l over here.

00:02:08.259 --> 00:02:09.870
Minus 2l.

00:02:09.870 --> 00:02:12.070
You're also going to have to do
that on the left-hand side.

00:02:12.070 --> 00:02:15.400
So you're going to
have minus 2l.

00:02:15.400 --> 00:02:18.060
We're doing it on both sides
of the equation.

00:02:18.060 --> 00:02:21.180
And remember, an equation says
P is equal to that, so if you

00:02:21.180 --> 00:02:23.570
do anything to that, you
have to do it to P.

00:02:23.570 --> 00:02:25.780
So if you subtract 2l from this,
you're going to have to

00:02:25.780 --> 00:02:28.950
subtract 2l from P in order
for the equality

00:02:28.950 --> 00:02:31.260
to keep being true.

00:02:31.260 --> 00:02:39.450
So the left-hand side is going
to be P minus 2l, and then

00:02:39.450 --> 00:02:43.250
that is going to be equal to--
well, 2l minus 2l, the whole

00:02:43.250 --> 00:02:46.150
reason why we subtracted 2l is
because these are going to

00:02:46.150 --> 00:02:47.280
cancel out.

00:02:47.280 --> 00:02:49.350
So these cancel out,
and you're just

00:02:49.350 --> 00:02:51.870
left with a 2w here.

00:02:51.870 --> 00:02:54.170
You're just left with a 2w.

00:02:54.170 --> 00:02:55.260
We're almost there.

00:02:55.260 --> 00:02:58.250
We've almost solved for w.

00:02:58.250 --> 00:03:00.990
To finish it up, we just have
to divide both sides of this

00:03:00.990 --> 00:03:02.350
equation by 2.

00:03:02.350 --> 00:03:05.510
And the whole reason why I'm
dividing both sides of this

00:03:05.510 --> 00:03:09.400
equation by 2 is to get rid of
this 2 coefficient, this 2

00:03:09.400 --> 00:03:11.830
that's multiplying w.

00:03:11.830 --> 00:03:15.770
So if you divide both sides of
this equation by 2, once

00:03:15.770 --> 00:03:17.780
again, if you do something to
one side of the equation, you

00:03:17.780 --> 00:03:19.260
do it to the other side.

00:03:19.260 --> 00:03:22.330
The whole reason why I divided
the right-hand side by 2 is 2

00:03:22.330 --> 00:03:25.120
times anything divided by 2
is just going to be that

00:03:25.120 --> 00:03:27.240
anything, so this is
going to be a w.

00:03:27.240 --> 00:03:29.240
And then we have our
left-hand side.

00:03:29.240 --> 00:03:31.300
So we're done.

00:03:31.300 --> 00:03:38.240
If we flip these two sides, we
have our w will be equal to

00:03:38.240 --> 00:03:45.830
this thing over here-- equals
P minus 2l, all

00:03:45.830 --> 00:03:50.700
of that over 2.

00:03:50.700 --> 00:03:52.830
Now, this is the
correct answer.

00:03:52.830 --> 00:03:54.990
There's other ways to
write it, though.

00:03:54.990 --> 00:03:58.610
You might want to rewrite this,
